                                     {
                                         "text":  "This result is an approximation, which will be refined as we study Earth further in the Atlas.\n\n#### We Are All Stardust\n\nPlanets form from clouds of dust, just like stars (<htcite0>).\n\nAt the beginning of this process, the amount of dust particles is very small. As the cloud collapses, dust grains move closer and collide, forming larger clusters known as planetesimals (<htcite1>; <htcite2>; <htcite3>).\n\n#### Planet Growth\n\nThese planetesimals continue to collide with other particles, giving rise to an even larger structure known as a protoplanet.\n\nOver time, the protoplanet accumulates more material and eventually reaches the stage of a fully formed planet (<htcite4>).",
